Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.50,0:00:49.66,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 它没呼吸了 快点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ah, it's not breathing. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.25,0:00:51.32,中文,,0,0,0,,稻草\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Straw.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.23,0:00:59.26,中文,,0,0,0,,清干净了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.27,0:01:01.33,中文,,0,0,0,,继续啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Keep trying!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.33,0:01:03.32,中文,,0,0,0,,快点 快点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:23.22,中文,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.22,0:01:25.18,中文,,0,0,0,,看到没\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}See!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.21,0:01:29.19,中文,,0,0,0,,新生命\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}New life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.18,0:01:37.20,中文,,0,0,0,,儿子 把牛奶拿到马车上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Get milk on cart, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:39.21,中文,,0,0,0,,否则我们会错过六点的火车\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Or we'll miss six o'clock train.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.16,0:01:43.16,中文,,0,0,0,,每天都如此 从不间断\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Every day without fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.16,0:01:45.20,中文,,0,0,0,,必须赶上六点的火车\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'the six o'clock train had to be caught.'
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.21,0:01:47.82,中文,,0,0,0,,错过火车 牛奶场就会\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Miss the train and the dairy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.82,0:01:50.16,中文,,0,0,0,,与我们断绝联系  农场就会破产\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}would drop us and the farm would go under.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:51.23,中文,,0,0,0,,我们就完了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'We'd be finished.'
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.22,0:01:56.24,中文,,0,0,0,,走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.24,0:01:59.16,中文,,0,0,0,,继续 莫利\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go on, Molly!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.21,0:02:10.23,中文,,0,0,0,,再快点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Faster!'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.18,0:02:14.25,中文,,0,0,0,,再快点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Faster!'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:16.23,中文,,0,0,0,,再快点 快\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go faster, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.21,0:02:24.18,中文,,0,0,0,,距离战争结束已经五年了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'For five years, since the end of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.18,0:02:27.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我这一代人一直回视着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'my generation had been looking over their shoulders
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:30.18,中文,,0,0,0,,虽然已经去世但永远年轻的哥哥们的灵魂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'at the ghosts of older brothers who would always be young.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:44.23,中文,,0,0,0,,但前方一直在召唤我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'But up ahead calling me on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:49.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我的生活只求生存\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'there was my own life begging to be lived.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:03:00.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你身上都是泥巴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You're very... muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:16.21,中文,,0,0,0,,有的时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.21,0:03:22.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我听说过他 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I hear him, Bert.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:25.16,中文,,0,0,0,,并且我以为他没死\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And I think he's not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.18,0:03:28.18,中文,,0,0,0,,这很愚蠢吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is that foolish?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:34.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我可爱的男孩\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My lovely boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.25,0:03:38.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他说 创造一个更好的世界\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"Make a better world," He said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:03.24,中文,,0,0,0,,有些人有贵人保护\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Some people have saints for protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.24,0:04:05.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我会带着乔的照片的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll take Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.21,0:04:09.19,中文,,0,0,0,,小心点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.18,0:04:31.19,中文,,0,0,0,,上帝和你同在 伯特 米德尔顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}God go with you, Bert Middleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:40.17,中文,,0,0,0,,继续 小伙子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go on, lad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.16,0:05:06.23,中文,,0,0,0,,你那叫开车吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You call that driving?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.19,0:05:12.22,中文,,0,0,0,,看 野兔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Look. It's the hare!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.22,0:05:17.20,中文,,0,0,0,,从没有人完成它 伯特 那我将会是第一个 没错\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No-one's ever done it, Bert. I'll be the first, then. Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.20,0:05:20.16,中文,,0,0,0,,猎犬在这里 先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The hounds are here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.17,0:05:26.24,中文,,0,0,0,,感谢你的到来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Thanks for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.24,0:05:28.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我想你会好好享受这一天的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think you'll enjoy the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.25,0:05:30.20,中文,,0,0,0,,阿林汉姆大人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lord Allingham.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:11.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这个屋子的每个参观者名字都在这上 无一例外\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Every visitor to this house is in here, without exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.16,0:06:13.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我父亲坚持这样做\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My father insisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:16.25,中文,,0,0,0,,这是历史 他说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"It's history," He said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:20.16,中文,,0,0,0,,他死的时候 他住在三间屋子里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}When he died, he was living in three rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:26.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我向他保证过我给这里重新带来欢乐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I promised him I'd make it happy again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:30.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我们坚持做下去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.16,0:07:14.22,中文,,0,0,0,,他让仆人感到害怕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He frightens the servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:18.17,中文,,0,0,0,,他让首相都感到害怕 他拥有半条佛里特街\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He frightens the Prime Minister. He owns half of Fleet Street
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.17,0:07:20.19,中文,,0,0,0,,他是政党中的暗中操控者 母亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and he's the fixer in the party, mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.19,0:07:21.22,中文,,0,0,0,,取悦他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Make him happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.22,0:07:23.23,中文,,0,0,0,,你让我听起来像个妓女\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You make me sound like a common prostitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:25.18,中文,,0,0,0,,只是尽可能做到最好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Just do what you do best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.18,0:07:27.18,中文,,0,0,0,,怎么做 尽地主之仪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And what's that? Host.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:30.21,中文,,0,0,0,,不要相信一个睡在身上毛\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Never trust a man who sleeps with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.21,0:07:33.16,中文,,0,0,0,,比灰狗还多的东西旁的男人 波莉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}anything hairier than a greyhound, Polly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.16,0:07:35.77,中文,,0,0,0,,早上好 吉尔马丁 早上好 阿林汉姆夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good morning, Lord Kilmartin. Good morning, Lady Allingham.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:37.23,中文,,0,0,0,,你不知道我多高兴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I can't tell you how delighted I am
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.23,0:07:40.20,中文,,0,0,0,,因为今天你的驾到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that you're here on this day, of all days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.20,0:07:42.16,中文,,0,0,0,,希望如此\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I wish you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:47.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我很高兴今天你能光临\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I am delighted that you're here on this day of all days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:49.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你真迷人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You're a fascinating woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:52.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你已经是人夫了 吉尔马丁大人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And you're a married man, Lord Kilmartin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:56.16,中文,,0,0,0,,现在 最要紧的事就是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now, the pressing question is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.16,0:07:58.75,中文,,0,0,0,,你喜欢香肠吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..How do you like your sausage?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:08:00.17,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.18,0:08:06.16,中文,,0,0,0,,请\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:23.18,中文,,0,0,0,,我给你表演一下舞步\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll show you the steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.21,0:08:36.24,中文,,0,0,0,,乔治\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}George.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.24,0:08:39.20,中文,,0,0,0,,早餐之前来段舞 噢 棒极了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Dancing before breakfast? My, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:44.19,中文,,0,0,0,,来和你的妻子跳支舞吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come and dance with your wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:51.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我可以请你跳舞吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}May I have this dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:56.20,中文,,0,0,0,,一周前 我看见一个小男孩\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A week ago, I saw a small boy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.20,0:08:59.17,中文,,0,0,0,,把他的手指放进电灯插座里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}put his finger in an electric light socket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.17,0:09:01.21,中文,,0,0,0,,电击把他抛起穿过屋子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The shock threw him clean across the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.21,0:09:04.18,中文,,0,0,0,,当他起身时 他惊声尖笑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}When he got up, he was screaming with laughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:08.20,中文,,0,0,0,,电流 爱因斯坦 爵士乐 任何事都有可能 所以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Electricity, Einstein, jazz - anything is possible. So?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.20,0:09:11.22,中文,,0,0,0,,这是这个国家有史以来最重要的选举\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This is the most important election this country has ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.22,0:09:14.23,中文,,0,0,0,,吉尔马丁在这是因为他认定你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lord Kilmartin's here because he wants YOU!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.23,0:09:18.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你今天表现的好  那你将是下一届的内政大臣\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You play it right today, you'll be the next Home Secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.18,0:09:23.17,中文,,0,0,0,,大家日安\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Happy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.17,0:09:26.23,中文,,0,0,0,,已经十五年了 很多次我都认为\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's been 15 years and there have been times
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:29.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这再也不会发生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when I thought this would never happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.16,0:09:31.20,中文,,0,0,0,,所以 上帝保佑你们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So, God bless you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:36.20,中文,,0,0,0,,为了今天新来的客人  一个非常温暖的阿林汉姆式的欢迎\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}For those new to this day, a very warm Allingham welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.20,0:09:39.18,中文,,0,0,0,,有一首我们经常唱的赞美诗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now there's a hymn that we used to sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:40.30,中文,,0,0,0,,赞美诗没有改变 是吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hymns don't change, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.32,0:09:43.25,中文,,0,0,0,,因此 请和我一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So, please, join in with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:49.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我害怕没有反对者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# I fear no foe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.22,0:09:53.24,中文,,0,0,0,,和你一起祝福\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# With Thee at hand to bless
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.24,0:09:58.18,中文,,0,0,0,,我没有砝码\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# Ills have no weight
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.18,0:10:03.20,中文,,0,0,0,,眼泪没有怨恨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# And tears no bitterness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:07.22,中文,,0,0,0,,死亡刺痛哪儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# Where is death's sting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.22,0:10:12.18,中文,,0,0,0,,哪儿 墓穴 你的胜利\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# Where, grave, thy victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:15.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我还是成功了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# I triumph still
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.21,0:10:19.54,中文,,0,0,0,,你与我同在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}#If Thou abide with me. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:21.18,中文,,0,0,0,,躲藏者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:31.23,中文,,0,0,0,,围巾\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Handkerchief?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.23,0:10:33.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我们需要这上面的气味\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We'll need the scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.24,0:10:37.24,中文,,0,0,0,,把衬衫脱了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Shirt. Take it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:48.20,中文,,0,0,0,,味无芬芳的英格兰\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}England un-perfumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.20,0:10:52.16,中文,,0,0,0,,深呼吸 中世纪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Breathe deeply - the Middle Ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:54.20,中文,,0,0,0,,牛蒡 大麦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Burdock, barley,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.20,0:10:58.18,中文,,0,0,0,,猪鼻子 狗舌头 可能是吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}nose of pig's breath, dog's tongue, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.18,0:11:00.23,中文,,0,0,0,,哦 是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And... Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.23,0:11:02.22,中文,,0,0,0,,古老的乡下人的苦味\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ancient peasant bitterness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.24,0:11:07.16,中文,,0,0,0,,它是我兄弟的衬衣\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It was my brothers' shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.16,0:11:08.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他死了 他去世了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's dead. He died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:10.25,中文,,0,0,0,,从外观来看 看来你是经常穿着的了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Whilst wearing it, by the looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.25,0:11:13.20,中文,,0,0,0,,规则如下 开始后你有十分钟的时间\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The rules - you have a ten minute start.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.20,0:11:15.20,中文,,0,0,0,,当喇叭一吹响 我们就开始追逐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The horn blows when we begin the chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:16.33,中文,,0,0,0,,你必须待在阿林汉姆地界上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You must stay on Allingham
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.33,0:11:18.24,中文,,0,0,0,,或待在村庄的边界范围内\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}land or within the boundaries of the village
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:21.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你不能进任何屋子 明白吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and you must not step inside any house, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:23.18,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你活下来并且没被抓住的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}If you survive and you're still free
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.18,0:11:26.23,中文,,0,0,0,,当喇叭在一点钟再次吹响时 你就赢了  多少钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when the horn blows again at one o'clock you win. How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.23,0:11:27.24,中文,,0,0,0,,一磅\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A pound.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:32.17,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你在一点差三分时候 被吉尔马丁大人抓住的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And if you allow yourself to be caught by Lord Kilmartin
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:35.22,中文,,0,0,0,,那么在晨练后\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}at three minutes to one, after a good morning's sport,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.22,0:11:38.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我还是会给你一磅 为什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'll still give you a pound. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:41.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你不会懂的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.19,0:11:42.24,中文,,0,0,0,,再加点赌注\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Up the stakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:45.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他会付你两磅如果你能存活到早晨\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He'll pay you two pounds if you survive the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:48.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你觉得呢 阿林汉姆 够刺激才是王道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Won't you, Allingham? Incentive is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.20,0:11:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,当然 但是 如果他被抓住了 在余下的时间里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Of course. But, if he's caught, he'll do everything I ask of him
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.20,0:11:53.23,中文,,0,0,0,,他将听命于我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}for the rest of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.22,0:11:59.16,中文,,0,0,0,,五磅 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Five pounds. Bert...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:05.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你将是我的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You'll be mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:14.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我不能呆在这\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I can't stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.19,0:12:25.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这氛围\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I like it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.16,0:12:41.19,中文,,0,0,0,,走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.20,0:12:49.18,中文,,0,0,0,,跑呀 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Run, Bert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:11.21,中文,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.25,0:13:29.24,中文,,0,0,0,,朝着溪流\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Towards the stream!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.17,中文,,0,0,0,,多少钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.17,0:13:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,在谢菲尔德有份摄影助理的工作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's a job in Sheffield, for a photography assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.20,0:13:55.16,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我今天赢了 我就够去租个房了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And, if I win today, it's enough to set me up wi' lodgings
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.16,0:13:58.21,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们抓住你怎么办 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and everything. What if they catch you? Bert?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.20,0:14:02.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你不会让他们得逞的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You won't let 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.17,0:14:09.23,中文,,0,0,0,,闻起来很糟糕\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This smells terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.22,0:14:15.21,中文,,0,0,0,,走 走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.19,0:15:08.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他在哪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.17,0:15:13.19,中文,,0,0,0,,找到他 伙计们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Find him, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.22,0:16:11.20,中文,,0,0,0,,新出生的小牛 一小时之前\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}New calf - hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.20,0:16:15.17,中文,,0,0,0,,你应该想到的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You should have thought of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.19,0:16:18.25,中文,,0,0,0,,再给我一周时间\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Give me another week.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.21,0:16:23.22,中文,,0,0,0,,有点担当吧 米德尔顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Responsibility, Middleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.22,0:16:24.74,中文,,0,0,0,,我租给了你牛棚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I rented you the cowshed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.74,0:16:27.19,中文,,0,0,0,,都说好了每月三英镑的租金\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}we agreed the three pounds monthly rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.19,0:16:30.20,中文,,0,0,0,,可你没交 所以我要收回了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You haven't paid it, so I'm taking it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.20,0:16:32.24,中文,,0,0,0,,如果小牛死了 那是你的错 不是我的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your fault if the calf dies, not mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.18,0:16:39.20,中文,,0,0,0,,请你现在把你的动物弄出我的牛棚\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Get your animals out of my cowshed now, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.18,0:16:54.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这不是他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.16,0:17:01.21,中文,,0,0,0,,他在哪儿 他在哪儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where is he? WHERE IS HE?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.18,0:17:08.19,中文,,0,0,0,,快走 快走快走快走快走\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go! Go, go, go, go, go, go, go, go, go...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:30.16,中文,,0,0,0,,快走 接着走 走啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go on. Walk on. Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.21,0:17:58.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我爱你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.19,0:18:06.19,中文,,0,0,0,,快点儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:08.18,中文,,0,0,0,,快 快点儿啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Faster! Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.18,0:18:09.22,中文,,0,0,0,,到这下面来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Get down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.18,0:18:17.19,中文,,0,0,0,,喂 你 起来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oi, you, get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.19,0:18:19.16,中文,,0,0,0,,他在哪儿啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.16,0:18:21.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你又是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.18,0:18:28.22,中文,,0,0,0,,-你为什么这么做 -闭嘴 我问你个问题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-What did you do that for? -Shut up! I asked you a question!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.18,0:18:32.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你是聋子吗 孩子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Are you deaf, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:38.21,中文,,0,0,0,,抱歉 说错了 黑鬼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sorry, wrong word. Nigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.21,0:18:40.24,中文,,0,0,0,,再说一遍\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:42.23,中文,,0,0,0,,回答他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Answer him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.22,0:18:49.23,中文,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.23,0:18:52.19,中文,,0,0,0,,在上面 看啊 他在哪儿 是他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Up there, look! There he is! It's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:53.25,中文,,0,0,0,,快来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.25,0:19:04.24,中文,,0,0,0,,感觉就像你向我求婚的时候\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It feels like when you proposed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.24,0:19:07.17,中文,,0,0,0,,还记得吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.17,0:19:10.22,中文,,0,0,0,,风把你的帽子吹掉了 就在你正要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Wind blew your cap off just as you were about to...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:14.18,中文,,0,0,0,,他把牛棚收回了 小拉特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's taking cowshed back, young Rutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.18,0:19:18.19,中文,,0,0,0,,-他比他的父亲要混蛋多了 -为什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-He's twice the bastard his father ever was. -Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.19,0:19:19.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我们欠他租金\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We owe him rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:22.19,中文,,0,0,0,,-嗯 我们去哪儿挤奶呢 -在田野里\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-Well, where we going to do the milking? -In field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.19,0:19:24.22,中文,,0,0,0,,什么 一天两次吗  在冬天吗 约翰\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What, twice a day?! In winter, John?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:29.20,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 我们只是要早起一点 晚睡一点\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, we'll just have to get up earlier and go to bed later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.20,0:19:31.20,中文,,0,0,0,,然后用上帝给的每个小时工作\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And work every hour that God sends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.20,0:19:36.20,中文,,0,0,0,,八年来你每天都祈祷 他到底要什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You have prayed every day for eight years. What does he want?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.20,0:19:39.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你一无所得却还要继续付出\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}How much more are you going to give him for nothing in return?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:44.79,中文,,0,0,0,,事情一定会改变的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Something's got to change,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.80,0:19:47.25,中文,,0,0,0,,约翰 要这么做的是我们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}John, and it's us that've got to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.25,0:19:49.21,中文,,0,0,0,,小牛会死吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is the calf going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:53.51,中文,,0,0,0,,咱们把她带到田野里吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Let's get her up into field.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.51,0:19:56.16,中文,,0,0,0,,她最好和她妈妈在一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Her best chance is to be with her mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.16,0:19:59.17,中文,,0,0,0,,喝到前十二小时的初乳以免得病\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}get first 12 hours of milk to protect her from diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.17,0:20:03.20,中文,,0,0,0,,之后 如果她活下来了 我们可以在屋里用奶瓶喂她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And then, if she survives, we might bottle-feed her inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.20,0:20:04.24,中文,,0,0,0,,父亲不会让她死的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Father won't let her die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.22,0:20:10.23,中文,,0,0,0,,你捡起来了 我的帽子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You picked it up - my cap.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.17,0:20:15.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你把帽子给我戴上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You put it back on my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.22,0:20:18.22,中文,,0,0,0,,然后你说 是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and then you said yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.22,0:20:25.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我也爱你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I love you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.17,0:20:40.17,中文,,0,0,0,,他在那儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.16,0:20:49.18,中文,,0,0,0,,快来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:51.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我们就要抓到他了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We're on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.18,0:22:41.24,中文,,0,0,0,,-噢 先生 抱歉 -让开 该死的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-Oh! Sorry, sir. -Out of my way, damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.20,0:23:09.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你跑不了了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Got ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.22,0:23:17.17,中文,,0,0,0,,他也许能做到\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He might do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.17,0:23:21.21,中文,,0,0,0,,130年了 野兔从来没有幸存过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}130 years and a hare has never survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.22,0:23:33.19,中文,,0,0,0,,他在哪儿 他在哪儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where is he? Where is he!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.24,0:24:24.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你应该停下来在浴室洗个澡的 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You should have stopped for a wash in bath house, Bert.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.16,0:24:27.17,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 记得透过屋顶偷看的时光吗 那是我们多大\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Eh, remember that time looking through roof? How old were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.17,0:24:28.24,中文,,0,0,0,,12岁半\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}12 and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.24,0:24:32.18,中文,,0,0,0,,-你在看什么 -谁也没看 你在看谁 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-Who were you looking at? -Nobody. Who were you looking at, Bert?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.18,0:24:35.22,中文,,0,0,0,,那是过去的事了 不是吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's the thing about the past, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:39.19,中文,,0,0,0,,每次你看的时候 都会有更多的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Every time you look, there's more of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.19,0:24:41.22,中文,,0,0,0,,深刻 他真是思想深刻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So profound. He's so profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.22,0:24:44.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道的 你可以做老师的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You know, you could be a teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.19,0:24:46.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你最怀念童年的什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What do you miss most about childhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.19,0:24:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,歌声 曾经有更多的歌声\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Singing. There were more singing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.20,0:24:54.21,中文,,0,0,0,,母亲曾经用啤酒给我们洗头 我和乔伊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My mother used to wash our hair in beer - me and Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.24,0:25:04.21,中文,,0,0,0,,他会很为你骄傲的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He'd have been proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.16,0:25:22.20,中文,,0,0,0,,#我拿着钞票去了市场\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# As I was going to Darby Upon a market day
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.20,0:25:26.23,中文,,0,0,0,,#我看到了最大的公羊呀 是用干草喂的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}# I saw the biggest ram, sir That ever was fed on hay
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.23,0:25:28.13,中文,,0,0,0,,#是个谎言 是个谎言 是个谎言\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}#It's a lie, it's a lie It's a lie, a lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.13,0:25:30.24,中文,,0,0,0,,你赢了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you win?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.24,0:25:39.18,中文,,0,0,0,,不 他作弊了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No. He cheated!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.18,0:25:40.18,中文,,0,0,0,,作弊了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Cheated?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.18,0:25:43.24,中文,,0,0,0,,进入了一个村妇的前室 违反了所有规定\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Went into a village woman's front room, against all the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.24,0:25:50.20,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 那很好 那么 追猎者又赢了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, that's good, then. The hounds win again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.20,0:25:53.18,中文,,0,0,0,,-午饭吃什么 -鲑鱼\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-What's for lunch? -Trout.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.17,0:26:00.18,中文,,0,0,0,,伯特作弊了吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Bert cheated?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.18,0:26:02.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你听到那个人怎么说了 玛莎\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You heard what the man said, Martha.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.18,0:26:11.19,中文,,0,0,0,,欺骗 谎言 女士的前室\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Cheating, lies, ladies' front rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.19,0:26:14.24,中文,,0,0,0,,基尔马丁有这全部三种的天赋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Kilmartin has a talent for all three! I'm sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.24,0:26:16.23,中文,,0,0,0,,当基尔马丁向他女儿求婚时\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lord Chater was concerned when Kilmartin
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.23,0:26:17.94,中文,,0,0,0,,蔡特勋爵很担心\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}asked for his daughter's hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.94,0:26:20.21,中文,,0,0,0,,以为基尔马丁是为了政治目的这么做的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that he was after political advancement.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.21,0:26:23.19,中文,,0,0,0,,他错了 他是瞄准了他的整个家庭\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He was wrong. He was after his whole family!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.19,0:26:26.16,中文,,0,0,0,,到底是哪个家庭成员\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Which member of the family was he actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.16,0:26:28.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他事实上上了他的妻子 妻子的表妹\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's actually fucking his wife, his wife's cousin
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.24,0:26:30.22,中文,,0,0,0,,和他继子的妻子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and his stepdaughter-in-law!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.16,0:26:34.25,中文,,0,0,0,,蔡特勋爵不知道\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Chater doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.25,0:26:36.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他到底是什么样的人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What kind of a man is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.20,0:26:39.21,中文,,0,0,0,,半天 阿林厄姆 一个下午\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Half a day, Allingham, one afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.21,0:26:42.20,中文,,0,0,0,,让他保持微笑 你的职业生涯就会腾飞\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Keep him smiling and your career is launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.25,0:26:52.21,中文,,0,0,0,,抓住她 抓住她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hold. Hold her, hold her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.16,0:27:06.16,中文,,0,0,0,,还有件事 阿尔伯特 爱因斯坦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And another thing, Albert Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:07.22,中文,,0,0,0,,谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.22,0:27:09.23,中文,,0,0,0,,不再是以前的那个时代了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Time is not what it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.23,0:27:13.23,中文,,0,0,0,,这不是我们能用来衡量一切的常数\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's not a constant against which we can all measure everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.23,0:27:15.22,中文,,0,0,0,,它是相对的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It is relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.22,0:27:17.21,中文,,0,0,0,,所以我们只能靠自己 我们每个人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So we're on our own, all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.21,0:27:20.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你要说什么 他在说些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What are you on about? What's he on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.25,0:27:23.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他说重要的是要留下自己的印记\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's saying it's important to leave your mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.19,0:27:37.20,中文,,0,0,0,,你去哪了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.20,0:27:38.23,中文,,0,0,0,,我赢了五英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I've won five pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.19,0:27:42.20,中文,,0,0,0,,妈妈\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.20,0:27:46.16,中文,,0,0,0,,-你拿到了么 -承诺给我了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-Have you got it? -Promised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.16,0:27:47.24,中文,,0,0,0,,告诉她\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.17,0:27:51.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我赢了五英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I've won five pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.18,0:27:56.24,中文,,0,0,0,,是他的钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.20,0:28:00.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是你的钱 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's your money, Bert.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.19,0:28:39.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我们欠拉特多少钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}How much do we owe Rutter?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.25,0:28:42.20,中文,,0,0,0,,三英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Three pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.22,0:28:45.22,中文,,0,0,0,,不 太晚了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.21,0:28:49.25,中文,,0,0,0,,-租期什么时候到期 -今天\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-When's rent due? -Today.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.20,0:28:54.16,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 今天还没结束 对吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, today's not over, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.23,0:29:14.22,中文,,0,0,0,,脱下夹克\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Jacket off.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.22,0:29:17.18,中文,,0,0,0,,民有的男人不会觉得冷\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A man of the people doesn't feel the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.22,0:29:41.17,中文,,0,0,0,,国会开幕典礼 国王的演讲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The State Opening of Parliament, the King's Speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.17,0:29:43.21,中文,,0,0,0,,圣诞早晨 我自己的生日\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Christmas morning, my own birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.21,0:29:46.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我愿意放弃掉所有这些以换取我们村子这一特殊的日子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'd give them all up for this special day in our village.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.22,0:29:51.17,中文,,0,0,0,,-300来 一位阿林汉姆 -他让我想起我父亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-For 300 years, an Allingham... -He reminds me of my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.17,0:29:52.50,中文,,0,0,0,,站在了我站的地方\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..Has stood where I now
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.50,0:29:55.16,中文,,0,0,0,,让这个美好的传统继续流传\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}stand and kept this wonderful tradition alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.16,0:29:58.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们一度远离这里 我们都是 我们一度被考验\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We've been away for a while, we all have, and we've been tested,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.24,0:30:02.22,中文,,0,0,0,,但我们通过了考验 而今天 今天标志着\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but we have come through and today, today marks the return of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.22,0:30:06.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我们为之奋战的英式生活的回归\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that English way of life we've all been fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.22,0:30:14.20,中文,,0,0,0,,谢谢 享受着一天  祝好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Thank you. Enjoy the day. Box well.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.19,0:30:23.20,中文,,0,0,0,,感谢你们来 谢谢 很高兴见到你们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Thank you for coming along. Thank you. Lovely to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.20,0:30:28.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我叫比利吉比\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}My name's Bill Gibby.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:32.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我想问两个问题\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And I want to ask two questions:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.21,0:30:36.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我是谁 你是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who am I? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:40.16,中文,,0,0,0,,试着把两个问题都回答了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And try to answer them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.16,0:30:44.20,中文,,0,0,0,,在这里我是局外人 但我知道这个国家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm an outsider here. But I know this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.20,0:30:46.22,中文,,0,0,0,,肺脏 我们市民是这么称呼这个地方的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"The lung" Us townsfolk call the place
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.22,0:30:48.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你们很幸运地把这个地方叫做家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you're fortunate enough to call home.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.25,0:30:52.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我曾每周日来这儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And I used to come up here every Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.17,0:30:54.71,中文,,0,0,0,,我是为了这里的空气来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It was my coming up for air,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.71,0:30:58.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我花了6年挖矿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}for the six years I spent mining coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.16,0:31:00.19,中文,,0,0,0,,之后我又花了4年\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Then I had another four years
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.19,0:31:03.25,中文,,0,0,0,,在德国的线路下挖土设置爆炸物\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}digging under the German lines to set explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.25,0:31:06.22,中文,,0,0,0,,这种生活艰难吗 也许\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Has it been a tough life? Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.22,0:31:11.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得我自己悲惨吗 一点也不\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Do I feel sorry for meself? Not a bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.21,0:31:14.16,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我知道一件事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Cos if there's one thing I know,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:17.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我们不会获得真正的自由\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}it's that none of us will be free
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.20,0:31:19.42,中文,,0,0,0,,除非我们自己\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}until we stop thinking of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.42,0:31:23.17,中文,,0,0,0,,不再视自己为受害者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}ourselves as victims and become masters...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.17,0:31:28.16,中文,,0,0,0,,-和情人 -并成为自己生命和未来的主人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- and mistresses - of our own lives and our own futures.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.16,0:31:36.18,中文,,0,0,0,,这有一首诗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here's a poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.18,0:31:40.18,中文,,0,0,0,,英国人 荣誉的传人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Men of England, heirs of Glory
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.23,0:31:44.25,中文,,0,0,0,,未来故事里的英雄\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Heroes of unwritten story
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.22,0:31:49.18,中文,,0,0,0,,伟大母亲的后裔 \N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Nurslings of one mighty Mother 
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.18,0:31:51.18,中文,,0,0,0,,她的希望 互为希冀\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hopes of her, and one another
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.18,0:31:54.20,中文,,0,0,0,,像雄狮一般苏醒崛起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Rise like Lions after slumber
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.20,0:31:56.21,中文,,0,0,0,,不可征服的一群勇士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}In unvanquishable number
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.22,0:31:59.24,中文,,0,0,0,,像抖掉露珠般\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Shake your chains to earth like dew
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.24,0:32:03.18,中文,,0,0,0,,抖落你沉睡时被套上的枷锁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Which in sleep had fallen on you -
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.22,0:32:09.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你们千万人 他们一小撮\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Ye are many - they are few.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.20,0:32:15.24,中文,,0,0,0,,雪莉能为我解答\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Shelley has the answer to my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.24,0:32:19.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我是谁 你是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who am I? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.22,0:32:21.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我们是一体的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We are one!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.25,0:32:25.21,中文,,0,0,0,,团结一致 我们便所向无敌\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And together, we are unvanquishable!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.18,0:32:42.17,中文,,0,0,0,,说得好 先生 干得漂亮\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well said, sir. Very well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.24,0:32:52.17,中文,,0,0,0,,来自暗黑大陆的丛林最深处\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here from the deepest jungle of the darkest continent
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.17,0:32:56.18,中文,,0,0,0,,为你挑选最佳勇士\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}for you to pit your best men against.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.18,0:33:00.23,中文,,0,0,0,,谁有勇气来接受挑战\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who has the courage to take on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.23,0:33:03.18,中文,,0,0,0,,萨维奇 阿菲利加\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Savage Africa?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.19,0:33:13.24,中文,,0,0,0,,153场比赛的不败神话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}153 fights undefeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.24,0:33:17.22,中文,,0,0,0,,谁会是第一个击败萨维奇 阿菲利加的人呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who will be the first man to beat Savage Africa?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.22,0:33:19.20,中文,,0,0,0,,上 去赢走你的钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go and get your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.18,0:33:22.25,中文,,0,0,0,,谁会是第一个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who's first?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.25,0:33:29.16,中文,,0,0,0,,能打上一回合 赢得 一英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Survive a round and win... A pound!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.16,0:33:34.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我们的第一位挑战者   站起来吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Our first contender, step right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.17,0:33:36.19,中文,,0,0,0,,大家掌声鼓励\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Give him a round of applause, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.18,0:33:51.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你作弊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You cheated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.24,0:33:57.20,中文,,0,0,0,,抱歉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.23,0:34:18.22,中文,,0,0,0,,伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Bert?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.18,0:34:22.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他们说我作弊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They said I cheated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.22,0:34:25.21,中文,,0,0,0,,-但你没有  -当然没有\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-But you didn't. -No!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.21,0:34:27.17,中文,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.17,0:34:33.16,中文,,0,0,0,,一边基尔马丁勋爵 艾德蒙 阿林汉姆  一边是我和你 算了吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lord Kilmartin, Edmund Allingham, me and you? Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.21,0:34:40.24,中文,,0,0,0,,在军队里我可是拳击冠军\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I was boxing champ in the army, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.24,0:34:44.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我要你帮我做点事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}There's something I want you to do for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.17,0:34:48.16,中文,,0,0,0,,多少？\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.22,0:35:22.20,中文,,0,0,0,,一 二 三 四 五\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}One, two, three, four, five,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.20,0:35:26.22,中文,,0,0,0,,六 七 八 九\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}six, seven, eight, nine,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.22,0:35:30.18,中文,,0,0,0,,十 比赛结束\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}ten. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.20,0:35:54.08,中文,,0,0,0,,如果把牛犊留在田里一整夜的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Our calf will die of cold
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.08,0:35:57.18,中文,,0,0,0,,牛犊会被冻死的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}if she's left out in the field all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.18,0:36:03.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道你不喜欢我丈夫 或者我们全家\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I... I know you don't like my husband, or our family,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.22,0:36:08.16,中文,,0,0,0,,但是 求求你 今晚让我们用一下牛棚好吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but PLEASE can we have the cowshed tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.21,0:36:15.20,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我给你加时的话，下星期又会是怎样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}If I give you extra time, what will it be next week?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.20,0:36:16.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你不能一直这样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You can't go on like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.18,0:36:21.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我想这也是你会在这里的原因\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I think that's why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.19,0:36:31.25,中文,,0,0,0,,小牛需要温暖\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The calf needs warmth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.25,0:36:33.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我也需要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.21,0:36:36.22,中文,,0,0,0,,-抱歉 我听不懂  -不 你懂的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-Sorry, but I don't understand... -Yes, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.22,0:36:37.63,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么不是你的丈夫来找我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why didn't your husband
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.63,0:36:40.20,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你没有这个意思的话\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}come to see me if it weren't on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.19,0:36:45.17,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个邀请\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's an offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.16,0:37:21.21,中文,,0,0,0,,上个星期六我在博尔索佛见过他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I saw him last Saturday up at Bolsover Colliery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.21,0:37:26.18,中文,,0,0,0,,15名矿工一个接着一个上 他把他们都击倒了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}15 miners one after the other and he put them all down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.18,0:37:27.25,中文,,0,0,0,,下一个是谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who is next?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.25,0:37:32.23,中文,,0,0,0,,打赢一回合并赢得一英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Survive a round and win a pound!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.23,0:37:36.18,中文,,0,0,0,,英格兰人 是狮子还是羔羊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Men of England, are you lions or lambs?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.22,0:37:40.16,中文,,0,0,0,,好吧 两英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}All right, two pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.22,0:37:42.25,中文,,0,0,0,,还是没人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Still nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.25,0:37:46.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我从未给过这么样的奖品         3英镑\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here's an offer I've never made before, three pounds!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.16,0:37:50.18,中文,,0,0,0,,上来吧 他们全都试着打赢他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Step right up. They're all trying to fight him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.18,0:37:52.30,中文,,0,0,0,,你不需要打赢他   你只要撑上一回合\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You don't need to fight him, you just need to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.32,0:37:55.22,中文,,0,0,0,,约翰  不要鼓励他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}John?! Don't encourage him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.22,0:37:57.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我们需要那钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We need the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.20,0:38:01.17,中文,,0,0,0,,来吧 先生\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on, gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.22,0:38:07.22,中文,,0,0,0,,动起来 就像我教你的那样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Move your feet, like I taught you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.25,0:38:47.17,中文,,0,0,0,,加油 儿子 打倒他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Move, son! Knock him down!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.19,0:38:54.17,中文,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.20,0:39:04.19,中文,,0,0,0,,加油   打他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on! Hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.17,0:39:12.22,中文,,0,0,0,,动起来 伯特\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Move, Bert!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.20,0:39:17.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我不想打死你 躺下来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't want to kill ya. Go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.24,0:39:29.18,中文,,0,0,0,,一  二    三\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.18,0:39:31.22,中文,,0,0,0,,站起来      四\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on! ..Four...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.21,0:39:37.24,中文,,0,0,0,,五    六\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..Five, six...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.18,0:39:42.22,中文,,0,0,0,,七\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..Seven...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.21,0:39:48.19,中文,,0,0,0,,八\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..Eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.19,0:39:53.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你还好吗 儿子   要继续吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You all right, son? Do you want to go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.22,0:39:58.24,中文,,0,0,0,,没事吧       他没事   他没事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You all right? He's all right, he's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.19,0:40:07.19,中文,,0,0,0,,继续 伯特 加油 打他\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Keep moving, Bert. Come on! Hit him!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.19,0:40:17.19,中文,,0,0,0,,击倒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Knock out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.22,0:40:22.16,中文,,0,0,0,,胜利者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Winner!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.20,0:40:30.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你他妈的在打什么啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What the fuck are you playing at, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.16,0:40:41.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你儿子  是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your boy? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.18,0:40:44.20,中文,,0,0,0,,-他叫什么名字  -伯特 米德尔顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-What's his name? -Bert Middleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.18,0:40:51.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是那个王八蛋吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.18,0:40:55.22,中文,,0,0,0,,-他会打败你  -不 他不会\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}-He'll knock you down. -No, he won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.22,0:40:57.24,中文,,0,0,0,,不 他会\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Yes, he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.22,0:41:01.24,中文,,0,0,0,,谁说的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Who says?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.24,0:41:46.21,中文,,0,0,0,,不 他违规了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No! That was below the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.23,0:41:52.18,中文,,0,0,0,,一  二\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.18,0:41:56.20,中文,,0,0,0,,三   四\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}three, four...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.20,0:41:59.24,中文,,0,0,0,,五     六\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}five, six...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.24,0:42:02.18,中文,,0,0,0,,七  八\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}seven, eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.18,0:42:03.23,中文,,0,0,0,,站起来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.23,0:42:06.20,中文,,0,0,0,,九    躺下去  躺下去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}nine... Stay down! Stay down!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.21,0:42:32.20,中文,,0,0,0,,结束了 孩子 待在这  比赛结束了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's over, son. Stay there. It's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.19,0:42:37.18,中文,,0,0,0,,胜利者\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The winner!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.23,0:42:44.16,中文,,0,0,0,,我从没输过\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, I never.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.16,0:42:46.20,中文,,0,0,0,,基尔马丁宝刀未老\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Good old Kilmartin.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.18,0:42:52.20,中文,,0,0,0,,恭喜你  太了不起了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Congratulations. Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.18,0:43:00.20,中文,,0,0,0,,20英镑 为了你的败北\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}20 pounds, for you to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.20,0:43:06.21,中文,,0,0,0,,但 天啊 你不能败倒在这20英镑之下\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But, oh no, you can't fall over for 20 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.21,0:43:08.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会放弃任何一场比赛\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I won't throw a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.21,0:43:11.22,中文,,0,0,0,,这不是拳击\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This is not boxing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.22,0:43:14.21,中文,,0,0,0,,这是娱乐业  而我是制片人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}This is showbusiness and I'm the producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:18.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我不要你的臭钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't want your dirty money.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.18,0:43:24.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我也不需要你\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And I don't need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.25,0:43:27.23,中文,,0,0,0,,真的吗 好\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Really? Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.23,0:43:30.17,中文,,0,0,0,,把我的东西还给我然后滚蛋\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Give me what's mine and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.17,0:43:32.22,中文,,0,0,0,,手套 短裤 靴子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Gloves, shorts, boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.18,0:43:53.16,中文,,0,0,0,,走啊 你可以走了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Go on, then. Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.16,0:44:28.19,中文,,0,0,0,,进来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.18,0:44:34.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你没有妻子的 艾德蒙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You've no wife, Edmund.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.20,0:44:49.17,中文,,0,0,0,,关于基尔马丁勋爵我们知道些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So, what do we know about Lord Kilmartin?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.25,0:44:54.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他是个土霸王\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He's a bully
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.24,0:44:57.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是个骗子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and a cheat
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.19,0:45:00.18,中文,,0,0,0,,还有 他是你最好的朋友\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}and he's your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.18,0:45:02.19,中文,,0,0,0,,他会安排我进内阁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He'll put me in the Cabinet.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.22,0:45:04.75,中文,,0,0,0,,重要的是得到了权利\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's what you do when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.75,0:45:07.20,中文,,0,0,0,,过程并不重要\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}in power that matters, not how you get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.20,0:45:10.16,中文,,0,0,0,,这得看你为了权利伤害了谁\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That depends on who you hurt getting there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.16,0:45:12.18,中文,,0,0,0,,还有你的良心\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And your conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.16,0:45:18.25,中文,,0,0,0,,重音应该放在 鸡 上面还是 酒 上面\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Does one put the stress on "Cock" Or "Tail"?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.25,0:45:22.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是鸡 尾酒 还是鸡尾 酒 呢？\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Is it cockTAIL or COCKtail?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.19,0:45:24.25,中文,,0,0,0,,不管怎样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.16,0:45:29.16,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mm...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.16,0:45:33.21,中文,,0,0,0,,天啊 真是好喝得吓人啊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, this is... appalling
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.25,0:45:37.20,中文,,0,0,0,,艾德温娜 蒙巴顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Edwina Mountbatten.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.20,0:45:40.17,中文,,0,0,0,,绝对的性欲狂\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Absolute maniac for sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.17,0:45:42.19,中文,,0,0,0,,千万别和艾德温娜搭同一辆车  哦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Do not get in a taxi with Edwina. Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.16,0:45:48.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我离开一下 阿林汉姆夫人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Will you excuse me a moment, Lady Allingham?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.18,0:45:55.24,中文,,0,0,0,,她对你好吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Was she nice to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.24,0:45:57.23,中文,,0,0,0,,我发现芳香的衰落是如此的醉人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I find fragrant decay so moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.20,0:46:02.21,中文,,0,0,0,,她就像夏日最有一朵三色堇花\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}She's like the last pansy of summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.22,0:46:11.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你为什么倒下了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why didn't you go down?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.22,0:46:15.18,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我傻\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.18,0:46:16.22,中文,,0,0,0,,是勇敢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.22,0:46:18.18,中文,,0,0,0,,两者都有吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Maybe both.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.16,0:46:21.20,中文,,0,0,0,,像战场上的英国兵那样\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Like Tommies in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.21,0:46:28.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你是不是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.21,0:46:35.17,中文,,0,0,0,,那是为了什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What was it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.17,0:46:36.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我为了我的国家而战\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I fought for me country,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.21,0:46:39.22,中文,,0,0,0,,但在那之后他们不让我继续打拳击赛\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but they won't let me fight for boxing titles after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.22,0:46:41.21,中文,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.75,0:46:45.24,中文,,0,0,0,,因为我的肤色\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Because of the colour of me skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.20,0:46:50.23,中文,,0,0,0,,至少我熬过来了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}At least I got through it, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.18,0:47:02.16,中文,,0,0,0,,那是乔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's our Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.17,0:47:07.20,中文,,0,0,0,,黎明时被射死\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Shot at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.24,0:47:13.20,中文,,0,0,0,,就发生在我最好朋友身上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It happened to me best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.25,0:47:21.25,中文,,0,0,0,,他们派了个人拿着瓶威士忌\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}They send a man in, after the priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.25,0:47:24.24,中文,,0,0,0,,跟在神父之后进来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}with a bottle of whisky.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.24,0:47:27.21,中文,,0,0,0,,就算为了让他醉倒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}The idea is to get him so drunk that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.21,0:47:30.21,中文,,0,0,0,,让他死的时候毫无所觉\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}when dawn comes he hardly knows what's happening to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.18,0:47:37.20,中文,,0,0,0,,那晚我整晚陪在他身边\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I stayed with him all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.23,0:47:43.18,中文,,0,0,0,,但他不怕 也不喝酒\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}But he weren't afraid and he wouldn't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.16,0:47:50.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我不想在生命的最后时刻仍意识不清\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"I don't want to spend me last hours unconscious."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.23,0:47:55.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你当时和他在一起么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You were with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.16,0:48:00.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我半夜的时候进去了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I went in at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.22,0:48:08.21,中文,,0,0,0,,他说他热爱生命 现在还剩下为数不多的时间\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He said that he loved life and there's some of it left,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.21,0:48:13.22,中文,,0,0,0,,所以我们不会把时间浪费在谈论死亡的问题上\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}so we won't waste it talking about death and dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.22,0:48:17.19,中文,,0,0,0,,那 那你们都谈论了些什么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}What... What did you talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.19,0:48:19.20,中文,,0,0,0,,他的家人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}His family.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.23,0:48:27.24,中文,,0,0,0,,他想让我告诉他的家人们 虽然他在世的时间并不长\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He wanted me to tell them that, although his life was short...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.16,0:48:35.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但是他很庆幸能和自己的家人们一起度过这段时光\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}..He were lucky to have shared it with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.16,0:49:04.21,中文,,0,0,0,,你那儿沾了一点泥巴\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You've got a bit of mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.19,0:49:09.20,中文,,0,0,0,,这儿 不是 来 过来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Here? No, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.24,0:49:44.17,中文,,0,0,0,,世界真是美好 妈妈\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Make it a better world, mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.25,0:50:25.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我们一起抽了根烟\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}We were having a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.17,0:50:26.22,中文,,0,0,0,,我们\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"We"?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.20,0:50:31.22,中文,,0,0,0,,这是你的演讲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Your speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.22,0:50:32.99,中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得我应该把这些逐字写下来\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I thought I should write
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.00,0:50:36.24,中文,,0,0,0,,以免你觉得有点 呃\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}it word for word in case you're feeling, er,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.24,0:50:40.21,中文,,0,0,0,,混乱 关于那个派对和其他事情\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}out of joint - party and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.20,0:51:02.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我知道在一个派对上讨论政治不合时宜\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I know this is a party and no place for politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.25,0:51:06.21,中文,,0,0,0,,可是 很快将会有一场选举\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}However... there is an election coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.21,0:51:09.16,中文,,0,0,0,,-我们会赢得这场选举 -听 听\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}- Which we'll win. - Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.16,0:51:11.52,中文,,0,0,0,,你们有些人可能听了与我党对立的工党今天的言论\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Some of you may have heard my Labour opponent speak today...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.55,0:51:13.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我可以来根香烟么\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Could I have a cigarette?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.20,0:51:15.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我不抽烟 不好意思 从我个人来说\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I don't smoke, sorry. ..Personally I
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.17,0:51:18.17,中文,,0,0,0,,我更喜欢看一场拳击比赛\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}was more interested in what I saw in the boxing ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.17,0:51:24.16,中文,,0,0,0,,主要是关于决心 毅力 勇气 -伯特米德尔顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Mainly determination, courage, pluck - Bert Middleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.16,0:51:27.18,中文,,0,0,0,,他并没有伙伴可以并肩作战 只有一个人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He wasn't in the ring with his comrades, it was him in there -
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.18,0:51:28.26,中文,,0,0,0,,只身一人 挑战不可能\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}alone and against the odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.29,0:51:32.16,中文,,0,0,0,,那才是人类的精神 是我们本身应该具有的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That's human spirit, that's what we're made of.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.16,0:51:35.25,中文,,0,0,0,,社会主义总是鼓吹说是为了大众的利益 其实不然\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Socialism pretends to be for the good of everyone. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.25,0:51:38.19,中文,,0,0,0,,那是人类进步的阻碍\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's a hand-brake on mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.19,0:51:40.08,中文,,0,0,0,,只有个人的努力\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's individual endeavour
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.08,0:51:43.18,中文,,0,0,0,,才能让这个国家成为一个\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}that will make this country into a nation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.18,0:51:45.99,中文,,0,0,0,,可以被大家称之为\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}about which it is still possible to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.99,0:51:48.24,中文,,0,0,0,,一个英雄的国度\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}"This is a land fit for heroes."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.24,0:51:51.23,中文,,0,0,0,,听啊听啊 那是我的儿子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Hear, hear. He's my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.18,0:52:03.21,中文,,0,0,0,,你之前说他是个骗子 现在又说他是个英雄\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You said he was a cheat, now a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.21,0:52:05.19,中文,,0,0,0,,到底是哪个呢\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Which is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.24,0:52:13.23,中文,,0,0,0,,他违反了规定 去了玛格丽特博登的房子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}He went into Margaret Boden's house in breach of the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.23,0:52:15.19,中文,,0,0,0,,我说的对吗 基尔马丁大人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Am I right, Lord Kilmartin?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.18,0:52:18.17,中文,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.17,0:52:26.16,中文,,0,0,0,,所以是你儿子的言论忤逆了王公贵族\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}So it's your son's word against that of a peer of the realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.16,0:52:31.16,中文,,0,0,0,,你就想把他交给基尔马丁大人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Then you'll be handing him over to Lord Kilmartin.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.16,0:52:33.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你是在赌你的运气\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}That WAS the wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.19,0:52:38.21,中文,,0,0,0,,埃德蒙\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Edmund?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.22,0:52:49.16,中文,,0,0,0,,给她钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Pay her.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.20,0:53:08.24,中文,,0,0,0,,米德尔顿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Middleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.24,0:53:11.18,中文,,0,0,0,,我从没忘记一个名字\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I never forget a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.21,0:53:59.22,中文,,0,0,0,,荣誉 是一个男人最重要的东西 男人绝不能容许侮辱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Honour, a man's name, not being embarrassed in public -
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.22,0:54:01.46,中文,,0,0,0,,每一件你和基尔马丁在意的事\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}everything that matters to Kilmartin and you,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.46,0:54:04.21,中文,,0,0,0,,你为了一个农村的孩子和他的母亲让他颜面尽失\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}you threw it in his face for a farm boy and his mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.21,0:54:05.48,中文,,0,0,0,,总有人得坚守原则\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Someone has to be principled,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.48,0:54:07.20,中文,,0,0,0,,贝尔斯托 我这么做是对的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Bairstow. It was the right thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.20,0:54:11.18,中文,,0,0,0,,也得有人坚守过去的原则 阿林厄姆\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}And someone has to see past principles, Allingham!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.19,0:54:31.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你来这儿是为了改变我的想法 是吧\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}You've come to make me change my mind, I suppose?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.18,0:54:36.24,中文,,0,0,0,,不 我是想让阿林厄姆小姐告诉Chater大人\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}No, I was thinking of asking Lady Allingham to tell Lord Chater
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.24,0:54:39.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你正在找他的家人的麻烦\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}which members of his family you're fucking.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.16,0:54:43.18,中文,,0,0,0,,你是在威胁我吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Are you blackmailing me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.18,0:54:45.20,中文,,0,0,0,,正是\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.24,0:54:49.19,中文,,0,0,0,,阿林厄姆小姐\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lady Allingham?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.19,0:54:50.23,中文,,0,0,0,,等一会行吗\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}A moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.18,0:54:56.24,中文,,0,0,0,,虚伪\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Bluff!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.24,0:54:59.16,中文,,0,0,0,,打给我\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.25,0:55:04.24,中文,,0,0,0,,基尔马丁大人要你第一个听到这个消息\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Lord Kilmartin wanted you to be the first to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.18,0:55:16.20,中文,,0,0,0,,我打算让你的儿子成为下一任内政大臣\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I'm going to make your son the next Home Secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.16,0:55:21.18,中文,,0,0,0,,嗷 我的上帝\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.24,0:55:26.19,中文,,0,0,0,,嗷 我的上帝\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Oh, my goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.21,0:55:37.18,中文,,0,0,0,,我已经 嗯\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}I've, erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.18,0:55:40.22,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯 我来是为了给你一样你一直要求的东西\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Well, I've come to give you what you've been asking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.19,0:55:54.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你在哪儿 去拿钱了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Where have you been? To get the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.22,0:55:55.25,中文,,0,0,0,,你拿到了吗 是的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you get it? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.25,0:55:59.22,中文,,0,0,0,,你付钱给拉特了吗 我为什么要那么做\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Did you pay Rutter? Why would I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.22,0:56:03.17,中文,,0,0,0,,它是你的了 伯特 这是你赚来的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}It's yours, Bert. You've earnt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.25,0:56:16.25,中文,,0,0,0,,父亲\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.25,0:56:18.19,中文,,0,0,0,,儿子\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.24,0:57:23.20,中文,,0,0,0,,情况变了 我们有麻烦了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Something had changed. We were in trouble -
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.20,0:57:27.17,中文,,0,0,0,,牛棚没了 冬天延长了 厨房里只有一个牛犊\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'no cowshed, more months of winter and a calf in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.17,0:57:30.18,中文,,0,0,0,,五磅可是一大笔钱\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'Five pounds was a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.18,0:57:32.69,中文,,0,0,0,,它可以支付一个散工一段时间的工资了\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'It would pay for casual labour for a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.69,0:57:34.20,中文,,0,0,0,,但是这也不够\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}but it wouldn't be enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.20,0:57:38.17,中文,,0,0,0,,但是和我的家人一起站在那儿\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'But standing there, with my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.17,0:57:40.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们知道我们相聚在一起\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'we knew we'd been brought together.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.25,0:57:43.25,中文,,0,0,0,,他会一直和我在一起的 -乔\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'He would always be with me - Joe -
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.25,0:57:47.22,中文,,0,0,0,,而且 像我的妈妈一样 我会一直倾听他的\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'and, like my mother, I would keep hearing him...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.22,0:57:50.24,中文,,0,0,0,,但我已经不再回首过去\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'But I'd stopped looking over my shoulder
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.24,0:57:56.18,中文,,0,0,0,,而是开始期待着 新的生活\N{\3c&H000000&\fs25}'and begun looking forward - to a new life.'
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.20,0:58:25.98,中文,,0,0,0,,
